This cookie policy is part of the Birch Solutions, ("Birch") privacy It covers the use of cookies between your device and our We also provide basic information on services we may use, who may also use cookies as part of their This policy does not cover their If you don’t wish to accept cookies from us, you should instruct your browser to refuse cookies from https: www.buildwithfern.com . In such a case, we may be unable to provide you with some of your desired content and What is a cookie? ​ A cookie is a small piece of data that a website stores on your device when you It typically contains information about the website itself, a unique identifier that allows the site to recognize your web browser when you return, additional data that serves the cookie’s purpose, and the lifespan of the cookie Cookies are used to enable certain features (e.g. logging in), track site usage (e.g. analytics), store your user settings (e.g. time zone, notification preferences), and to personalize your content (e.g. advertising, language). Cookies set by the website you are visiting are usually referred to as They typically only track your activity on that particular Cookies set by other sites and companies (i.e. third parties) are called cookies They can be used to track you on other websites that use the same Types of cookies and how we use them ​ Essential cookies ​ Essential cookies are crucial to your experience of a website, enabling core features like user logins, account management, shopping carts, and payment We use essential cookies to enable certain functions on our Performance cookies ​ Performance cookies track how you use a website during your Typically, this information is anonymous and aggregated, with information tracked across all site They help companies understand visitor usage patterns, identify and diagnose problems or errors their users may encounter, and make better strategic decisions in improving their audience’s overall website These cookies may be set by the website you’re visiting (first-party) or by They do not collect personal information about We use performance cookies on our Functionality cookies ​ Functionality cookies are used to collect information about your device and any settings you may configure on the website you’re visiting (like language and time zone settings). With this information, websites can provide you with customized, enhanced, or optimized content and These cookies may be set by the website you’re visiting (first-party) or by We do not use this type of cookie on our Targeting advertising cookies ​ Targeting advertising cookies help determine what promotional content is most relevant and appropriate to you and your Websites may use them to deliver targeted advertising or limit the number of times you see an This helps companies improve the effectiveness of their campaigns and the quality of content presented to These cookies may be set by the website you’re visiting (first-party) or by Targeting advertising cookies set by may be used to track you on other websites that use the same We use targeting advertising cookies on our Edit this page What is a cookie? Hero Journey Manifesto — Hero Journey Club 0 Skip to Content Open Menu Close Menu Open Menu Close Menu the Hero journey manifesto Last Updated These are sayings, advice, and quotes that we have heard from our community and have compiled into a A place to start if you’re just curious about what we stand for and why we’re This is a living, dynamic document and reflects the values of our It will change as we We are gamers who are working on our mental health, Our community is a space for healing, connection, belonging, and growth, through gaming and group Part 1: The Struggle, THE PAIN You are not You are not Depression and anxiety are expected — they are normal responses to a broken society that devalues our human needs and our sense of belonging they are reminders from ourselves that we are worth so much more they are callings to the lives that we yearn for but are not yet living they are forms of grief for the human connections we have traded for the pursuit of We buy things we don’t want, to impress people we don’t like, to fill the gaping hole within ourselves that was torn open by early messages that we are not When life gets hard and we get hurt, it’s tempting to put on lots of armor to protect But it’s hard to feel hugs when you have armor It can get heavy to carry it around with you We distract and numb ourselves with all sorts of coping mechanisms to avoid the discomforts of We push back, we lash out, we isolate, we overwhelm, we hurt others, we hurt ourselves, and we try to dull the A little too much or a little too often, those coping mechanisms become You aren’t an addict, you are a human in Start there at the Start with All emotions are important most are beautiful, some are difficult, but they all carry messages about things that are important to Don’t overanalyze and don’t stay too long in the Feel the Process them in your body and Let go of the outcome, and where possible, try to find a way to learn from difficult When the feelings are too difficult to bear, just focus on the simple things: first breathe, then try to move your It’s okay to ask for You’re going to be Sometimes our brain chemistry works against us and makes us More often than our innate neurochemistry, our psychological, social, and physical environments and the thoughts beliefs that we hold about them, are the things that harm Stress is a message that something in your life isn’t right and needs your It was an important adaptation for Sometimes your needs to adjust its sensitivity and sometimes it s picking up signals you don t Most of the time, the messages get garbled during processing, based on our own thoughts and Don’t get caught in the “worry ” You’re not You just need some Is something harming you or do you just think that it will harm you? Are you overreacting or is your intuition telling you that the situation is not serving your best interests? Part 2: The Growth You are a human, who needs support We are each on our own journey of healing yet we can walk those journeys alongside each Be your own Be the hero that you needed when you were younger and be the hero who you can look up to Find your path and help others on Everyone struggles from time to It’s Keep You are capable of a lot more than you You can endure even Growth is always possible cultivate the strength to see the path Resilience is Courage is the starting You can t shame yourself into being Everyone is on their own We are all equals, we are all imperfect, we are all Life is about people and the experiences you create with It’s okay if you don’t know where you’re going or what you’re Most of us don’t. Go find your people and create your joy, Surround yourself with people who remind you that you are enough and reciprocate their kindness Don’t do it The stories we tell have the power to But they also have the potential to break Be careful which story you choose to The things you say to yourself matter practice choosing to say the kind and loving versions of the Anxiety and excitement are the same neurochemical pathways what makes it one or the other is what you think of the When possible, reframe as Choose to believe that you have We all hurt and we all experience pain — that’s one of the unavoidable truths of Don t wish for an easier life wish for the strength to fully embrace the one you have, both the good and the Build the courage to endure the pain and let the grief open you up to immense You’re Weave your experience into the shared tapestry of human It might give someone hope down the When the scars begin to fade with age, let s trade stories and celebrate them Your life is a verb, not a You are not static or You are being you, doing you, and living your life in each moment as a constellation of all your past decisions and all of your future This is your Do what you love and do it Hold onto the people and ideas that you love and give you Have the courage to change the things that hold you Share your joy with others and whenever you get the chance, lift

Frequently asked questions | Open Source Observability Platform for Logs, Metrics, Traces, and More â Your Ultimate Dashboard for Alerts and Insights Features â¾ FAQs Pricing Blog Docs Star Fork Get started for free Star Frequently Asked Questions What are you folks building? We are building the easiest, most efficient and sophisticated observability tool to monitor all your applications and You get a unified view of logs, metrics and traces and ability to easily navigate and correlate We are building a tool that is easy to operate, has great UX, and that you can start with megabytes of data and scale to petabytes of You can run this tool using a single binary on your laptop with less than MB What is OpenObserve? OpenObserve is an observability platform that provides a unified view of logs, metrics and How do I send logs to OpenObserve? You can send logs to OpenObserve using log forwarders like Fluentd, Fluentbit, Vector, Logstash, Filebeat, cloudwatch logs using Kinesis Firehose or using the OpenObserve How do I send metrics data to OpenObserve? You can send metrics data to OpenObserve using prometheus API or using the OpenObserve Promethus, OTEL collector, telegraf and possibly more tools support the How can I ingest Amazon cloudwatch logs into OpenObserve? You can ingest amazon cloudwatch logs into OpenObserve by subscribing a cloudwatch to a kinesis firehose You can then use HTTP delivery of kinesis firehose to send any logs to How do I send traces to OpenObserve? You can use opentelemetry libraries to instrument your application and send traces to You can also use the OpenObserve API to send Do I need to install OpenObserve to use it? You can choose to install OpenObserve in your laptop locally, in your own infrastructure (kubernetes, aws, gcp, azure, heroku, etc) or use OpenObserve With OpenObserve cloud you do not have to worry about installing, maintaining and keep up OpenObserve OpenObserve cloud provides generous free tier suitable for most individuals and Where does OpenObserve store data? OpenObserve can store data on local disk or s3 when run in a single node In HA mode OpenObserve requires an object store to store You could use s3, GCS, minio, Azure blob and any other s3 compatible object OpenObserve stores its metadata in sled for single node installation and in etcd for HA Can I build dashboards in OpenObserve? Yes, You can build dashboards in For Logs and traces data you can use SQL like queries to build For metrics data you can use both PromQL and SQL to build You can have data from logs, metrics and traces in the same dashboard giving you a unified view of all Can OpenObserve send alerts? Yes, you can send alerts to many sources like slack, teams, prometheus alertmanager and OpenObserve can send alerts to various destinations using its highly configurable destination You can configure alerts using SQL like queries for logs and traces data and PromQL for metrics Is OpenObserve ? Yes, You can use OpenObserve in a You can create multiple organizations and each organization can have multiple Each organizations users and data are isolated for that Can I deploy OpenObserve on Kubernetes? Yes, You can use the official helm chart to deploy OpenObserve on What are ingest functions? Ingest functions in OpenObserve are created using VRL a javascript like Ingest functions can be used to parse, filter, transform and enrich data at the time of You can use ingest functions to parse logs, extract metrics from logs, filter logs, transform logs and Ingest functions run on the incoming data before it is stored in OpenObserve What are query functions? Query functions in OpenObserve are created using VRL a javascript like Query functions can be used to parse, filter, transform and enrich You can use query functions to parse logs, extract metrics from logs, filter logs, transform logs and Query functions are used at the time of query when data has already been ingested into Does OpenObserve provide a GUI? OpenObserve provide a very advanced You can use the WebUI to build dashboards, alerts, ingest functions, query functions and You can also use the WebUI to view logs, metrics and traces How does OpenObserve compare to Elasticsearch? OpenObserve can have lower storage cost than Elasticsearch and much lower operational burden to Due to stateless nodes, it can scale much faster than It has been written in rust and enjoys its high performance and low memory OpenObserve is also much easier to operate than It has been built specifically for observability use cases, while Elasticsearch was built as a text search engine being used for observability use Can I install OpenObserve on my laptop? Yes, You can install OpenObserve on your laptop and get started in under 2 Follow the quickstart guide in Why is OpenObserve cloud service so much lower in cost compared to others in the industry? FAQ’s – zivian Skip to the content zivian Menu For Physicians FAQ’s Contact Us Menu Close Menu For Physicians FAQ’s Contact Us For Physicians FAQ’s Contact Us Support All About Clinical Collaborations FAQs from NPs and PAs Getting Started with Zivian Health What is Zivian Health? Zivian Health is an administrative platform helping healthcare organizations find great collaborating physicians for their NPs and Zivian aims to make clinical collaborations more productive via a convenient and secure platform, regulatory expertise, and an empowering clinical What is a collaborating physician? A collaborating physician is an MD or DO who has agreed to “collaborate,” or supervise your clinical work in a given state or states where you are both Collaborating means fulfilling the legal requirements of a physician collaborating with an NP or Why do I need one? Most states require NPs and PAs to have a physician serve in this role, in order to help ensure you are meeting the standard of care, and support you when Other states have no requirement of a collaborating physician, or only require a collaborating physician for a specific duration or in certain prescribing Although a collaborating physician is not strictly required for all NPs and PAs, at Zivian Health we believe a productive collaboration can bring tremendous value to many clinicians and How are we supposed to “collaborate”? The key components of a collaborating relationship can vary depending on your State regulations, your organization’s expectations, your clinical specialty, your scope of practice, and the professional relationship you However, some common features include: A collaborating agreement : a contract between you and your collaborating physician that includes both of your responsibilities, and an outline of your clinical protocol : meeting with your provider at a regular cadence, typically via teleconference Advice : your collaborator must be available to answer your medical and patient care questions Chart review : in most contexts, your physician will be required to conduct a specified number of monthly chart What should my Zivian Health collaborator know about? Whether your collaborating physician works with Zivian Health or at the same organization as you, they should be familiar with your practice protocols, expectations, and patient When should I go to my collaborator for help? Your collaborating physician will help you with your clinical questions, both about specific patients and about your medical Even if they do not know the answer to a question, Zivian Health has a very diverse roster of specialists whom your collaborator can rely on for additional Many collaborators will also be helpful in sharing advice on your professional development!
